               <msContents>
                  <summary>P. 1: Illumination of two saints. Excerpt from Four Gospels (Story of five loaves and two fishes) (pp. 2-3). Pp. 4 ff: Epistles of Paul, መልእክታተ፡ ጳውሎስ፡. Romans (p. 4); 1 Corinthians (p. 52); Illumination of two saints (p. 103); 2 Corinthians (p. 104); Illumination of two saints (p. 135); Galatians (p. 136). Illumination of two saints (p. 153); Ephesians (p. 154); Illumination of Saints Paul and Timothy (p 169); Philippians (p. 170); Illumination of two saints (p. 181); Colossians (p. 182); Illumination of Saints Paul, Silvanus, and Timothy; 1 Thessalonians (p. 194); 2 Thessalonians (p. 201); 1 Timothy (p. 206); Illumination of Paul and Timothy (p. 213); 2 Timothy (p. 214); A loose folio from Philemon (pp. 128-129); Titus (p. 230);  A folio from 2 Timothy (pp. 232-233); Titus resumed (234-235). Hebrews chapter 9 (p. 236-237). The remainder of the book is bound in disarray from 238-239. Illumination of Saint Paul (p. 243). Illumination of Saint Paul (p. 245). Hebrews (p. 246). Illumination of Saint John the Evangelist (p. 279). Beginning of the Gospel of Mark, in a different 15th century hand (p. 280); Illumination o fa saint (p. 281).  </summary>
                  
                  
               </msContents>
